I believe this is a duplicate.  We did not handle OutOfMemoryError during
shutdown in 2.1 properly.  This caused the tree to become corrupt and it would
not be possible to restart it.  This has been fixed.  Please reopen in
encountered in Eclipse 3.0 M1 or later.

Also, I would recommend increasing the java heap size allocated to Eclipse, like
this:

eclipse -vmargs -Xmx256M
